"{\"uid\": \"newsus.cgtn.com-news-2024-07-27-Steve-Dainton-discusses-table-tennis-expectations-for-Paris-2024-1vz5BP5RPxK-p.html\", \"text\": \"Our Privacy Statement & Cookie Policy  By continuing to browse our site you agree to our use of cookies, revised Privacy Policy and Terms of Use. You can change your cookie settings through your browser.  CGTN  Copied  When it comes to table tennis at the Paris Olympics, China will once again be the nation to beat.They have won 32 of the 37 gold medals on offer since the sport made its Olympic debut in 1998.  The legendary Ma Long will be looking for a sixth Olympic gold medal. Although he missed out on a spot on China\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s singles team, he was picked for the team event.  Steve Dainton is the head of the International Table Tennis Federation. He told CGTN\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Dan Williams that if Long achieves that sixth gold, it would cement his place as the greatest player of all time.  For more, check out our exclusive content onCGTN Nowand subscribe to our weekly newsletter,The China Report.  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466\"}"